OL,4,CCivil servant who worked for Greensill
OL,5,Crejects 'double hatting' label
OL,6, An ex-civil servant who worked for
OL,7, Greensill Capital and the government at
OL,8, the same time says he "followed the
OL,9, rules" and did nothing wrong.
OL,11,FJohn Crothers said his work for the now
OL,12,Fcollapsed finance firm had been "very
OL,13,Fpart-time" - and he only held two roles
OL,14,Ffor a three month period.
OL,16,F"In the press the phrase 'double
OL,17,Fhatting' has been used and I just feel
OL,18,Fthat is not appropriate," he told MPs.
OL,20,FHis decisions had been influenced by
OL,21,Fthe late Sir Jeremy Heywood, he added.
